@Acehaidrey 
The way how I work around it is to subclass [AppLoader](http://docs.celeryproject.org/en/latest/_modules/celery/loaders/app.html#AppLoader) and set the configs that I need in `config_from_object` after calling the method from super.
It is then possible to override the default Celery loader with environment variable `CELERY_LOADER`.

@ronfung 
> q1: If I want to set the logger hander to TimedRotatingFileHandler(other standard python handler), so far, not following how to specify it. Please help.

This PR uses standard Python dictionary logging config. For more detail, please see https://docs.python.org/2/library/logging.config.html#dictionary-schema-details.
If you want to use TimedRotatingFileHandler, I believe this will work:
```
'handlers': {
    'my.rotating.file.handler': {
        'class': 'logging.TimedRotatingFileHandler',
        'formatter': 'airflow.task',
        'filename': ...,
        <other optional TimedRotatingFileHandler params>
    },
}
```
